# Stack & Architecture Conventions

## Stack
- Next.js App Router (v16), React 19, TypeScript strict mode
- Supabase (`@supabase/supabase-js`, `@supabase/ssr`)
- React Query (`@tanstack/react-query`)
- `next-intl`, Tailwind CSS v4, Vitest + Testing Library, ESLint flat config

## Code organization (current pattern)
- `src/app`: routes/layouts (locale-aware)
- `src/components`: UI and feature components
- `src/api`: client-facing API wrappers/hooks
- `src/actions`: server actions
- `src/lib`: shared infra utilities (i18n, routes, supabase clients, helpers)

## Conventions
- Use TypeScript `type` over `interface` unless technically required
- Keep imports ordered and grouped; prefer type-only imports
- Use double quotes
- Follow existing naming and folder patterns before introducing new ones

## Architecture stance
- Do not introduce large architecture changes without user approval.
- If boundaries are unclear (e.g. `api` vs `actions`), propose 1-2 options with trade-offs.
